  "body": "> As a user\r\n> I want to be able to quickly scroll to the bottom of a chat\r\n> so that I can quickly jump to the newest messages\r\n> \r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWhen scrolling up in a chat, an icon should appear that if clicked, will bring the user back to the top of the chat.\r\n\r\nThis only includes the arrow, no counter.\r\n\r\n### Designs\r\n\r\n[https://www.figma.com/file/PPWkgOYlZZDxZv5SDGsZVV/Posts-%26-Attachments?node-id=4417%3A519126](https://www.figma.com/file/PPWkgOYlZZDxZv5SDGsZVV/Posts-%26-Attachments?node-id=4417%3A519126)\r\n\r\n### Known issues\r\n\r\nThere's no way to disable autoscroll, so if you are scrolling up in the chat history, and you receive a new message, it will offset the view, that's a know issue and will only be solved by changes in RN or a flat list replacement.",
